{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PtxtAeUhr594pAWGu58xfy","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I now have a comprehensive understanding of the HTTP routing in this Go project. Let me compile my findings.\n\n## Summary: HTTP Routing and Handler Architecture in Cloche\n\nI've thoroughly searched the codebase and found all HTTP routing definitions, endpoints, and frontend code. Here are my findings:\n\n### 1. **Where Routes Are Defined**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 139-158)\n\nThe routes are defined in the `NewHandler()` function using Go 1.22+ HTTP routing with `http.ServeMux`:\n\n```go\nh.mux := http.NewServeMux()\nh.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /{$}\", h.handleProjectOverview)\nh.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /runs\", h.handleRunsList)\nh.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /runs/{id}\", h.handleRunDetail)\nh.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /projects/{name}\", h.handleProjectDetail)\n// ... and more\n```\n\n### 2. **The \"Runs\" Endpoint**\n\n**HTML Routes:**\n- `GET /runs` - Lists all runs (with optional `?project=` filter)\n  - Handler: `handleRunsList()` (line 248)\n  - Template: `internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`\n\n- `GET /runs/{id}` - Shows detailed view of a single run\n  - Handler: `handleRunDetail()` (line 376)\n  - Template: `internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n\n**API Routes:**\n- `GET /api/runs` - JSON list of all runs (with optional `?project=` filter)\n  - Handler: `handleAPIRuns()` (line 447)\n  \n- `GET /api/runs/{id}` - JSON detail of a single run\n  - Handler: `handleAPIRunDetail()` (line 525)\n  \n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` - Fetch step output logs\n  - Handler: `handleAPIStepOutput()` (line 563)\n  \n- `DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container` - Delete a retained container\n  - Handler: `handleAPIDeleteContainer()` (line 636)\n  \n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` - Server-Sent Events stream of live logs\n  - Handler: `handleAPIStream()` (line 716)\n\n### 3. **The \"Projects\" Endpoint**\n\n**HTML Routes:**\n- `GET /` - Projects overview page (landing page)\n  - Handler: `handleProjectOverview()` (line 186)\n  - Template: `internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html`\n\n- `GET /projects/{name}` - Detailed project view with orchestrator control\n  - Handler: `handleProjectDetail()` (line 835)\n  - Template: `internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n\n**API Routes:**\n- `GET /api/projects` - JSON list of all projects with health stats\n  - Handler: `handleAPIProjects()` (line 474)\n\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/trigger` - Trigger orchestrator for a project\n  - Handler: `handleAPITriggerOrchestrator()` (line 674)\n\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator` - Get orchestrator status\n  - Handler: `handleAPIOrchestratorStatus()` (line 863)\n\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/start` - Enable orchestrator\n  - Handler: `handleAPIOrchestratorStart()` (line 882)\n\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/stop` - Disable orchestrator\n  - Handler: `handleAPIOrchestratorStop()` (line 898)\n\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency` - Set concurrency limit\n  - Handler: `handleAPIOrchestratorConcurrency()` (line 914)\n\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/info` - Project metadata (Docker image, version, prompts)\n  - Handler: `handleAPIProjectInfo()` (line 939)\n\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff` - Fetch git diff for a prompt file\n  - Handler: `handleAPIPromptDiff()` (line 1027)\n\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows` - List workflows for a project\n  - Handler: `handleAPIWorkflows()` (line 1058)\n\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` - Get step content\n  - Handler: `handleAPIStepContent()` (line 1134)\n\n**Static Routes:**\n- `GET /static/*` - Serves CSS and other static assets\n  - File: `internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\n### 4. **Frontend Code Linking to URLs**\n\n**Template Files with URL References:**\n\n**projects.html:**\n- `/projects/{{.Label}}` - Link to project detail page (line 9)\n- `/runs?project={{.Dir}}` - View runs filtered by project (line 27)\n- `/api/projects/{label}/trigger` - JavaScript fetch call (line 44)\n\n**runs.html:**\n- `/runs/{{.ID}}` - Link to individual run detail (lines 31, 84)\n- `/runs?project={{.Dir}}` - Filter runs by project (line 55)\n- `/api/runs` - Fetch runs list JSON (line 63)\n\n**run_detail.html:**\n- `/runs` - Back link to runs list (line 3)\n- `/api/runs/{id}/stream` - EventSource for live logs (line 103)\n- `/api/runs/{id}` - Fetch run updates (line 128)\n- `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` - Fetch step output (line 225)\n- `/api/runs/{id}/container` - Delete container (line 194)\n\n**project_detail.html:**\n- `/` - Back link to projects (line 2)\n- `/runs/{{.ID}}` - Link to individual runs (line 6)\n- `/runs?project={{.Dir}}` - View all project runs (line 8)\n- `/api/projects/{label}/orchestrator` - Fetch orchestrator status (line 56)\n- `/api/projects/{label}/orchestrator/{start|stop}` - Control orchestrator (lines 75)\n- `/api/projects/{label}/orchestrator/concurrency` - Set concurrency (line 82)\n- `/api/projects/{label}/info` - Fetch project info (line 90)\n- `/api/projects/{label}/info/prompt-diff` - Fetch prompt diff (line 131)\n- `/api/projects/{label}/workflows` - List workflows (line 143)\n- `/api/projects/{label}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` - Get step content (line 274)\n\n### 5. **Handler Setup in Daemon**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (lines 102-126)\n\nThe web handler is initialized and bound to an HTTP server:\n```go\nif httpAddr := envOrConfig(\"CLOCHE_HTTP\", globalCfg.Daemon.HTTP, \"\"); httpAddr != \"\" {\n    webHandler, err := web.NewHandler(store, store, webOpts...)\n    httpServer = &http.Server{Addr: httpAddr, Handler: webHandler}\n    go func() {\n        if err := httpServer.ListenAndServe(); err != nil && err != http.ErrServerClosed {\n            // error handling\n        }\n    }()\n}\n```\n\nThe HTTP server address is configurable via `CLOCHE_HTTP` environment variable.\n\n### 6. **Key Architecture Details**\n\n- **Mux Type:** `http.ServeMux` (Go 1.22+ style routing with `GET /path`, `POST /path` patterns)\n- **Handler Pattern:** Method receivers on a `Handler` struct that implements `http.Handler`\n- **ServeHTTP Method:** Line 163-165 delegates to the internal mux\n- **Template System:** Embedded HTML templates using Go's `html/template` package with custom template functions\n- **Static Assets:** Embedded CSS in `static/style.css` served via `http.FileServerFS`\n\nAll files are in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/` directory, which is the web adapter in the hexagonal architecture."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae5c40eb38f56e41d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 56233\ntool_uses: 17\nduration_ms: 29031</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aced3543-5ed5-4523-b8de-7b978353a1a0","uuid":"c02f9585-002b-4eb7-a6db-95dc66fc4c2d","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all files related to HTTP routing/handlers in this Go project. I need to understand:\n1. Where routes are defined (look for http.HandleFunc, mux, router patterns)\n2. How the \"runs\" endpoint is currently served (look for \"/runs\" path patterns)\n3. How the \"projects\" endpoint is currently served\n4. Any templates or frontend code that links to runs URLs\n\nSearch thoroughly - check cmd/, internal/, and any web/template directories.","agentId":"ae5c40eb38f56e41d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I now have a comprehensive understanding of the HTTP routing in this Go project. Let me compile my findings.\n\n## Summary: HTTP Routing and Handler Architecture in Cloche\n\nI've thoroughly searched the codebase and found all HTTP routing definitions, endpoints, and frontend code. Here are my findings:\n\n### 1. **Where Routes Are Defined**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (li